rComments: 1 of the best professors I've had so far. His eyes would always light up when teaching and it honestly made a world of a difference listening to him teach political ecology so passionately. Very kind, actually likes his students and loves to engage in class discussion. He makes sure you understand, is clear, gives good examples, has great stories.
Both readings and lecture are heavy with occasional pop quizzes, but he's an amazing lecturer! Very passionate.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: A very inspirational professor. If someone needs clarification he is willing to take time to explain concepts one on one. He fosters intellectual discussion and is open to learning from his students. A lot of reading but he is fair

This class was amazing. One of my favorite classes and professor thus far. He knows how to keep students from falling asleep and being bored. He is really invested in what he teaches and wants you to do well. Guaranteed A if you go to class and do the readings.  He provided all the readings online, which obviously is a plus because broke life.

Upside:Genuinely nice guy, incredibly helpful and understanding. Excited about teaching. Downside: uses difficult diction, terrible at communicating ideas in a precise and simplistic manner (can't teach to save his life). I have had D-level courses that are easier to comprehend in-comparison to his B-level course.

He's very passionate about his subjects. He's always smiling and very helpful. You can tell that he's a very intellectual man from the way he speaks in class. I recommend attending every class, taking everything down (although there is a lot of material!), and there will be a guaranteed A+.

Simply an amazing prof! He is one prof that really knows how to lead a discussion. Most of all, he is so warm and open to hearing people speak. I learned so much in that one semester. He truly loves what he is doing. The course is very fair, a lot of essays and a straight forward exam.
